## 2. Color System — Palette v3.1 (Locked)

### 2.1 Base Palette

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `--vx-bg` | `#0D0D0D` | Primary background — locked |
| `--vx-surface` | `#141414` | Card / panel / topbar backgrounds |
| `--vx-surface-2` | `#1A1A1A` | Nested surfaces, input fields, score tracks |
| `--vx-border` | `#1F1F1F` | Borders, dividers, subtle lines |
| `--vx-border-2` | `#2A2A2A` | Hover borders, emphasis lines |
| `--vx-white` | `#FFFFFF` | Primary text |
| `--vx-muted` | `#6B6B6B` | Secondary text, labels |
| `--vx-dim` | `#3A3A3A` | Disabled states, placeholders, decorative labels |

> Background is #0D0D0D — not pure black (#000000). True black is reserved for specific elements (e.g. PRIME badge fill). Use #0D0D0D for all page backgrounds.

### 2.2 State Colors — v3.1 (Locked 2026-06-02)

The palette encodes behavioral energy level. The color temperature narrative:
- **Dark blue** (Compression) = coiled, contained energy
- **Cyan** (Expansion) = burst releasing
- **Teal** (Traversal) = active directional move
- **Near-white** (Exhaustion) = spent, fading
- **Silver-gray** (Neutral) = ambient, no edge
- **Purple** (Failed) = structural failure — outside the energy spectrum
- **Gold** (PRIME) = the singular high-conviction signal

| State | Token | Hex | Energy | Symbol |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Traversal | `--vx-traversal` | `#00BFA5` | Active directional | ▲▲ |
| Expansion | `--vx-expansion` | `#26C6DA` | Burst breakout | ▲ |
| Compression | `--vx-compress` | `#4A7EC7` | Coil before release | ◉ |
| Exhaustion | `--vx-exhaust` | `#E8E8F0` | Move spent, fading | — |
| Neutral / Drift | `--vx-neutral` | `#A0AAB9` | Ambient, no edge | ~ |
| Failed Traversal | `--vx-failed` | `#9575CD` | Commitment broke | ✕ |
| ◆ PRIME signal | `--vx-prime` | `#D4A853` | All conditions aligned | ◆ |

**Exhaustion rendering rule:** #E8E8F0 is near-white. On dark backgrounds it MUST have a 1px border at rgba(232,232,240,0.25) minimum so the badge doesn't disappear. Never render Exhaustion without a visible border.

**PRIME rendering rule:** ◆ PRIME always appears alongside the state badge — never replaces it. Always gold. Always the diamond prefix character ◆.

**State colors are not directional.** They encode behavioral state, not price direction. Purple (Failed) does not mean short. Teal (Traversal) does not mean long. This distinction matters for onboarding copy and must never be violated in UI labels.

