## 7. Layout Principles

**Grid:** 1px gaps between panels (background color bleeds through as the divider). No thick borders between sections.

**Density:** Data-dense but not cluttered. Each panel should answer one question — state, sync, or memory. Never mix concerns in one panel.

**Topbar:** Always present. Contains wordmark (left), session context (center), status indicator (right). Height: 40px.

**Bottom bar:** Session statistics in JetBrains Mono. Version reference right-aligned.

**Panels:** Three-column grid for the main data area (state/scores, sync/context, memory zones). Stack vertically on narrow viewports.

**Spacing:** 14–16px padding inside panels. 8px between rows within a panel. 1px between panels (grid gap).

---

## 8. What NOT To Do

- No white or light backgrounds
- No drop shadows, glow, or blur effects
- No border-radius > 6px on any element
- No color-mixing between state colors in the same badge
- No bold text at body size — 400–500 weight only
- Do not use state colors for general UI decoration — only for their named state
- Do not label any state as bullish or bearish — they encode behavioral energy, not direction
- Do not show PRIME without the ◆ prefix character
- Do not render Exhaustion (#E8E8F0) without a visible border
- Do not use #000000 as the page background — use #0D0D0D
- Do not approximate the palette — use exact hex values from Section 2

